data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt-in to sync-over-async behavior, but in EF Core 11 that opt-in no longer exists — all synchronous calls **always throw** at runtime, with no workaround.

Your affected methods: `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()`.

### Fix: Convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will require making callers async as well (`async Task` up the call chain). There is no way to keep synchronous signatures with the Cosmos provider in EF Core 11.

**Tracking issue:** https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
